# Git hygiene and change scope

## Branches

- **One concern per branch/PR** — name reflects the feature (`feature/relay-p2p-connection`), not vague prep labels.
- **Delete remote branches** after merge (or when abandoned). Do not leave stale remotes; offer to delete when work is merged or dropped.
- **Do not push new commits to a branch after its PR merged** — open a new branch for follow-up work.

## Commits and PRs

- **Encapsulated changes only** — each commit/PR should map to one coherent unit of work that fits the project spirit (local-first, P2P, minimal scope).
- **No broad grab-bag PRs** — do not mix unrelated items (e.g. relay feature + git audit + placeholder cleanup) in one PR.
- **Ask before committing** unless the user explicitly asked for a commit. Do not auto-commit audit reports, policy files, or large doc dumps without review.

## Before acting

- Confirm the user has seen findings before creating commits or opening PRs for non-trivial work.
- Split unrelated work into separate branches from `development`.
